      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is a mechanically sound example of the iconic wide-body 996. Powered by a naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six, this engine has been proactively serviced with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The 6-speed manual Getrag transmission provides crisp synchronization across all ratios, delivering power through a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system. The chassis retains its factory-spec handling characteristics thanks to a refreshed multi-link rear suspension and Bilstein dampers. Braking performance is sharp, utilizing the 'Big Red' four-piston monobloc calipers and ventilated rotors. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the vehicle remains structurally excellent with no compromise to its aerodynamic efficiency or torsional rigidity. A true driver\u2019s car with a visceral exhaust note and communicative hydraulic steering.",
